-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Ever notice how stupid people seem to be doing great?
They get the jobs, the money, the followers, the hoes .... while the rest of us overthink ourselves into paralysis. 

Maybe it‚Äôs not luck. Maybe the world has changed what it rewards. In this episode, we talk about how modern life rewards confidence over competence, and whether being ‚Äúsmart‚Äù has actually become a disadvantage.

title: why modern relationships feel so broken (and how to fix them)
description:
üëâ Enjoyed this episode? There's way more unfiltered, unhinged and uncensored content on our Patreon. Click here to join the community and spiral with us: www.patreon.com/bobosvoid

   Follow us on Instagram/TikTok/Youtube @bobos.void
     Email us love letters (or hate mail): bobosvoidpod@gmail.com
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

we've inherited all these complicated rules about what love is supposed to look like: live together, split bills, share a bed, never think about anyone else, raise kids in a neat little nuclear family etc...

In this episode, we argue for something simpler: that the real foundation of love is freedom, not possession.

From sex to money to family structures, we talk about how relationships might look if we freed them from all the unnecessary rules.

This week we're talking about why it feels like everyone else is doing better than you. Spoiler: They're not.

Maybe we just all feel this way because we're comparing ourselves to people running a race that's rigged? Between school religion, kids jobs that shouldn't even exist and now even ghost jobs (yes, fake job listings).

Let's get into the comparison trap, the myth of success and why the whole system is basically one giant fraud.

title: metamorphosis by franz kafka (FULL AUDIO) l bedtime story
description:
part 2 coming soon!

okay so yesterday i was thinking about how i wanna bring back bedtime stories, belly rubs and naps. And; im also learning to give myself the romance i expect from others. So here we go: a bedtime story - From me to you :)

this is actually my favourite story of all time, and also the first book we're reading in the Book Club: Metamorphosis by Franz Kafka. It's about a guy, Gregor Samsa, who wakes up one morning, as a bug (lol mood).

I hope this absurdist-existentialist story about alienation, family and the torture of capitalism can soothe your anxiety and help you sleep better at night.

ALSO; dont forget - my first book club meeting is on Saturday December 12th at 3pm EST. We'll be discussing Part I (and maybe Part II) of metamorphosis. All details are on my patreon: www.patreon.com/bobosvoid

P.S I'm definitely not a good actor or by any means a professional storyteller, but hope u enjoy falling asleep to absurdism :))))))

Summary:
"The Metamorphosis" is a novella by Franz Kafka, first published in 1915 and one of his best known works. The story begins with a traveling salesman, Gregor Samsa, waking to find himself transformed into a horrible verminous creature. Terrifying in its banal simplicity, it became one of the seminal works of the twentieth century.
